definition: to wind up/to bring to an end/to finish
to receive/to accept/to collect/to put away/to restrain/to stop/in care of (used on address line after name)
tail/remainder/remnant/extremity/sixth of the 28 constellations/classifier for fish
horse's tail/pointed posterior section of a locust etc
final (i.e. final consonant or stop of some syllables in Asian phonetics)

sentences.english: After a player's wrap-up step is over, the next player begins his or her start phase.
sentences.chinese: 收尾工作结束后，下一个玩家开始他的开始阶段。

sentences.english: C. should be managed and controlled from project concept through close-out. close- out.
sentences.chinese: 从项目概念阶段到收尾阶段都应该加以管理和控制。

sentences.english: The night ended with a kick-ass party on the roof.
sentences.chinese: 万圣节在午夜屋顶派对大狂欢中收尾。

sentences.english: Every scene and every episode have been in service of the big wrap up.
sentences.chinese: 每一集每一个镜头都是为了最后的收尾。

sentences.english: In essence, you might end up with some sort of dementia.
sentences.chinese: 很可能的是，你会以痴呆收尾。

sentences.english: Mastering breakdancing involves learning a few finishing touches to add to your technique.
sentences.chinese: 霹雳涉及学习掌握一些收尾添加到你的技术。

sentences.english: Add the finishing touches with a custom soundtrack, voiceovers and titles.
sentences.chinese: 添加一个自定义的配乐，配音和字幕的收尾工作。

sentences.english: I asked him the reason, but he explained that his work was going to an end and he had more work to do during that period.
sentences.chinese: 问他原因，他说工作即将收尾，要做的事情很多。

sentences.english: The venture had no successful event.
sentences.chinese: 投机事业是没有成功的收尾。

sentences.english: According to Chinese tradition, the Lantern Festival is the last day of the Chinese New Year celebration.
sentences.chinese: 从中国民俗来说，元宵节是中国新春佳节的收尾。

sentences.english: I want to begin today with concluding Aristotle part3.
sentences.chinese: 我今天要以总结亚里士多德第三部曲收尾。

sentences.english: Having progressed smoothly, the project is currently in its phase-out period.
sentences.chinese: 目前项目进展顺利，并已进入收尾阶段。

sentences.english: The military exercise ended with a mock battle.
sentences.chinese: 这场军事演习以一场模拟战收尾。

sentences.english: I want to hear the bad news first, and I want to end on good news.
sentences.chinese: 我想先讲坏消息，然后以好消息收尾。

sentences.english: He worried that producer Dennis Herring might have too much control over the final sound of the songs.
sentences.chinese: 他担心制作人丹尼斯赫林对歌曲的收尾控制过多。

sentences.english: The letter ended on a cheerful note.
sentences.chinese: 这封信以乐观的口气收尾。

definition: final part of a go game (see 官子[guan1 zi3])/endgame/to finish up/to come to the final stage
shift in the trend of events/turnaround/plot shift in a book/turn in the conversation
to come to the end of a phase (idiom)
foreshadowing (literary device)/foretaste of material to come (in essay or story)
